olive oil
2 sprig spring onion
1 packet coriander
1 packet parsley
1 lemon
1 packet chilli flakes
2 avocado
1 packet sour cream
¼ tsp salt
¼ tsp pepper

• Thinly slice spring onion. Finely chop coriander and parsley. Zest lemon to
get a pinch and halve.

• In a medium bowl, combine coriander, parsley, a pinch of chilli flakes (if
using), juice of half the lemon, a generous pinch of salt and sugar and 2 tbs
olive oil. Set aside.

• Slice avocado in half and scoop out flesh. Place avocado in a small bowl
and mash with a fork.
• Add sour cream, spring onion, remaining lemon juice, lemon zest, the salt
and the pepper, and stir to combine. Season to taste.
TIP: For a smoother guacamole, use a food processor.

• Transfer creamy guacamole to a serving bowl. Spoon over salsa
verde. Enjoy!